what is difference between path variable and request param?
Ans:
@PathVariable: Extracts values directly embedded into the URI path itself.
Example URL: /users/45Spring Syntax: @GetMapping("/users/{id}")
@RequestParam: Extracts values from the query string appended after a question mark (?).
Example URL: /users?id=45Spring Syntax: @GetMapping("/users")

 // Using @PathVariable to find a specific user by ID
    @GetMapping("/users/{userId}")
    public ResponseEntity<User> getUserById(@PathVariable("userId") Long id) {
        return ResponseEntity.ok(userService.findById(id));
    }

    // Using @RequestParam to filter users by their role
    @GetMapping("/users")
    public ResponseEntity<List<User>> filterUsersByRole(
            @RequestParam(name = "role", required = false, defaultValue = "USER") String role) {
        return ResponseEntity.ok(userService.findByRole(role));
    }


